# Q1. What is the overall distribution of Transaction Amounts? Are there any outliers present?
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
df = pd.read_csv("bank_transactions_data.csv")
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.boxplot(x=df['TransactionAmount'], color='skyblue')
plt.title('Distribution of Transaction Amounts with Outliers')
plt.xlabel('Transaction Amount')
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

# Q2. What is the average transaction amount for each transaction type?
avg_by_type = df.groupby('TransactionType')['TransactionAmount'].mean().sort_values(ascending=False)
plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
avg_by_type.plot(kind='bar', color='teal')
plt.title('Average Transaction Amount by Transaction Type')
plt.xlabel('Transaction Type')
plt.ylabel('Average Amount')
plt.grid(True)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Q3. Which locations have the highest number of login attempts
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
login_counts = df.groupby('Location')['LoginAttempts'].sum().sort_values(ascending=False)
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
login_counts.head(10).plot(kind='barh', color='darkorange')
plt.title('Top 10 Locations by Login Attempts')
plt.xlabel('Total Login Attempts')
plt.ylabel('Location')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# ✅ Q7. Which merchants are associated with the highest total transaction amount?

# Q10. Visualize relationships between numerical variables to identify fraud patterns
# Select numerical columns for pair plot
numerical_cols = ['TransactionAmount', 'AccountBalance', 'TransactionDuration', 'LoginAttempts']
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
sns.pairplot(df[numerical_cols], diag_kind='kde', plot_kws={'alpha': 0.5, 'color': sns.color_palette('Set3')[0]})
plt.suptitle('Pair Plot of Numerical Variables for Fraud Analysis', y=1.02)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
